linux-security-dashboard (4.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package release.
  * v4.2 features:
    - Hardware temperature checks via lm-sensors with threshold-aware findings.
    - SMART drive health checks via smartmontools (read-only -H, never -t).
    - Optional Timeshift snapshot before destructive actions; the action is
      aborted if the snapshot fails so the safety net is guaranteed.
    - RUN EVERYTHING chained assessment with a good/needs-fixing summary.
    - Offline detection for CVE lookups and tool installs.
    - Tools panel redesigned with category tabs and a cron scheduler card.
    - Lynis output streams line-by-line as the audit runs.
    - Persistent undo log; rollback matches on time+action+cmd+undo_cmd.

 -- playdoggs <playdoggs@users.noreply.github.com>  Sun, 27 Apr 2026 10:00:00 +1000
